addOrderBatch(bool[],uint128[],uint128[].details: notice here a batch of orders represented in arrays. order x is represented by x cells of all arrays.all arrays expected to the same length.

params.dstAmount: per each order. destination amount for order x.
params.hintPrevOrder: per each order what is the order it should be added after in ordered list. 0 for no hint.
params.isAfterPrevOrder: per each order, set true if should be added in list right after previous added order.
params.isEthToToken: per each order. is order x eth to token (= src is Eth) or vice versa.
params.srcAmount: per each order. source amount for order x.
